/themed environments, programmed events, volunteer travel opportunities, and visiting local communities by way of solidarity tourism and mission work. It includes a wide range of examples from Europe, the Middle East, Asia, Africa, Latin America and North America and will be of interest to researchers and students in religious studies, tourism, pilgrimage studies, geography, anthropology and Christianity studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aChristian pilgrims and pilgrimages. 0aPilgrims and pilgrimages. 0aSacred space. 0aTourismxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aTravelxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 4aChristian spirituality & religious experience. 4aChristianity. 4aTourism industry. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  aBiblical theme parks.  aChristian mega-events.  aChristian pilgrimage.  aChristian travel and tourism.  aChristianity.  aHeritage commodification.  aPilgrimage.  aReligion.  aReligious tourism .  aVolunteer Tourism .1 aTimothy, Dallen J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCVP eBook-Package Contemporary 2016-2020z978311075434640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184541665240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781845416652423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781845416652.jpg  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK